## Minimum CSS Reset

```css
*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

html {
  font-size: 16px;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
}

body {
  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: #1f2937;
  background-color: #f9fafb;
}

a {
  color: inherit;
  text-decoration: none;
}

button, input, textarea, select {
  font: inherit;
}

img, video, svg {
  display: block;
  max-width: 100%;
}

p, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  overflow-wrap: break-word;
}
```

The most critical: `box-sizing: border-box`. Without it, width calculations are nightmares.

Set `font: inherit` on form elements so they use your chosen font, not the system font.

Set `display: block` on images to eliminate the awkward baseline gap below inline images.

Use `-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased` for crisper fonts on Mac.

## Quick Exercise

Create a new HTML file with no styles. Add a heading, paragraph, link, button, and input. Look at what the browser gives you. Now add the reset above and see how much better your starting point is.

## Quick Recap

- Browser defaults are functional but not designed.
- `box-sizing: border-box` is the single most important reset.
- Form elements need `font: inherit` to use your chosen font.
- Images need `display: block` to eliminate baseline gaps.
- Tailwind's `@tailwind base` handles most resets for you.
